<h1>Privacy Policy – HMIS Mobile App (BGH Bokaro)</h1>
<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> March 2026</p>

<p>
The Centre for Development of Advanced Computing (C-DAC), Noida, is committed to protecting the privacy and security of users of the HMIS Mobile App implemented for Bokaro General Hospital (BGH) and associated health facilities under SAIL-Bokaro.
</p>

<p>
This Privacy Policy explains how user information is accessed, used, stored, and protected when using the HMIS Mobile App. This policy applies only to the HMIS Mobile App developed by C-DAC for Bokaro General Hospital and does not apply to other websites, services, or applications operated by SAIL or other organizations.
</p>


<div class="section">
<h2>1. Information We Access or Collect</h2>

<p>The HMIS Mobile App may access or process the following types of information in order to provide hospital services:</p>

<h3>Personal Information</h3>
<ul>
<li>Patient CR Number or Hospital Identification Number</li>
<li>Appointment and visit details</li>
<li>Prescription information</li>
<li>Hospital service records related to the patient</li>
</ul>

<h3>Health Data</h3>
<p>The application processes health-related information including:</p>

<ul>
<li>Consultation records</li>
<li>Medical prescriptions</li>
<li>Investigation or treatment details</li>
<li>Teleconsultation session information between doctor and patient</li>
</ul>

<p>This data is used strictly for providing hospital services through the HMIS system.</p>

<h3>Device Permissions</h3>

<p>The application may request the following permissions:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Camera:</strong> Used for video consultation between patients and doctors during teleconsultation workflows.</li>
<li><strong>Microphone:</strong> Used to enable communication between patients and doctors during teleconsultation.</li>
<li><strong>Storage/File Access:</strong> Used to download, store, and view prescriptions or other medical documents.</li>
</ul>

<p>These permissions can be revoked at any time from the mobile device settings.</p>

</div>


<div class="section">

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>

<p>The information accessed by the application is used solely for the following purposes:</p>

<ul>
<li>Managing hospital appointments</li>
<li>Enabling teleconsultation between doctors and patients</li>
<li>Accessing and viewing prescriptions and medical documents</li>
<li>Providing digital hospital services through the HMIS platform</li>
</ul>

<p>
The HMIS Mobile App does not sell, rent, or share user data with third parties for advertising or marketing purposes.
</p>

</div>


<div class="section">

<h2>3. Data Storage and Retention</h2>

<p>
User data processed through the HMIS Mobile App is stored securely within the Hospital Management Information System (HMIS) servers managed by authorized hospital infrastructure.
</p>

<p>
Health and medical records may be retained according to hospital record retention policies and applicable healthcare regulations.
</p>

<p>
The mobile application itself does not permanently store sensitive personal or health information except temporary files such as downloaded prescriptions required for viewing.
</p>

</div>


<div class="section">

<h2>4. Data Security</h2>

<p>
C-DAC implements appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect user information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
</p>

<p>
Communication between the mobile application and HMIS servers is secured using encrypted communication protocols.
</p>

</div>


<div class="section">

<h2>5. Data Deletion and User Rights</h2>

<p>
Users who wish to request correction or deletion of their personal data may contact the hospital administration or the HMIS support team.
</p>

<p>
Requests will be processed in accordance with hospital policies and applicable healthcare regulations.
</p>

<p>
Users may also delete locally stored documents such as downloaded prescriptions directly from their mobile device.
</p>

</div>


<div class="section">

<h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>
C-DAC may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in services, policies, or legal requirements.
</p>

<p>
When updates are made, the “Last Updated” date at the top of this page will be revised.
</p>

</div>


